For me AWB has to be Englands starting RB in the Euro's. TAA is great against poor opposition due to his attacking ability and less defensive work, more posession etc. I think he's very poor defensively I think TAA if he comes up against top top class teams like your Germany's, France's, Netherlands etc. I think he'll be massively exposed defensively.

AWB is outstanding defensively where we'll need to be if we face the top top teams due to a lack of posession and we do have to sit back 60/70% of a game.
